org.upmc.electisim

Class GenericMessageException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • org.upmc.electisim.GenericMessageException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AgentConfigurationException, CandidateConfigurationException, EmptyBufferException, InvalidExtensionException, InvalidStateSteppingException, ListenerNotFoundException, PreferencesInconsistencyException, SimulationProfileConfigurationException

    public class GenericMessageException
extends java.lang.Exception
    A class of exception which take a message at construction, which can be then used when the user wants to retrieve informations.

    The full message will be the message, with the stacktrace appender. The original message can be retrieved using the getMessage() method.

    Serialized Form
